00:14:45.229 --> 00:14:47.020
Now let's talk about
energy and propulsion.

00:14:47.020 --> 00:14:49.810
So for bus, the most
traditional thing

00:14:49.810 --> 00:14:53.217
is to have a diesel
internal combustion engine.

00:14:53.217 --> 00:14:54.800
It used to be the
conventional engine.

00:14:54.800 --> 00:14:57.580
Now they've really improved
with fuel injection

00:14:57.580 --> 00:14:59.110
and other technologies.

00:14:59.110 --> 00:15:00.840
They've made them clean diesel.

00:15:00.840 --> 00:15:02.980
So they control the exhaust.

00:15:02.980 --> 00:15:06.490
And these engines can shut
down and start very cleanly

00:15:06.490 --> 00:15:09.080
without wasting of fuel.

00:15:09.080 --> 00:15:13.390
So, they reduce
pollution and noise.

00:15:13.390 --> 00:15:17.380
There's compressed natural
gas and abbreviated CNG.

00:15:17.380 --> 00:15:21.010
A lot of the fleet here in
Boston, bus fleet, is CNG.

00:15:21.010 --> 00:15:22.330
And they're pretty loud.

00:15:22.330 --> 00:15:24.970
And they have a CNG
logo in the back.

00:15:24.970 --> 00:15:28.270
So you'll notice
when you see them.

00:15:28.270 --> 00:15:32.200
Those are-- they require special
maintenance and refueling

00:15:32.200 --> 00:15:33.790
facilities, of course.

00:15:33.790 --> 00:15:38.950
And, at least in North America,
CNG was popular for a while.

00:15:38.950 --> 00:15:41.310
But now agencies
are switching back

00:15:41.310 --> 00:15:44.040
to diesel, and in particular,
clean diesel and hybrid

00:15:44.040 --> 00:15:45.660
electric with diesel.

00:15:45.660 --> 00:15:48.556
So fully electric buses exist.

00:15:48.556 --> 00:15:49.680
And they're getting better.

00:15:49.680 --> 00:15:52.500
Battery energy storage
is getting better.

00:15:52.500 --> 00:15:56.900
So we have fully electric
buses that can service--

00:15:56.900 --> 00:15:59.040
that can provide
service for many hours

00:15:59.040 --> 00:16:00.520
without recharge in between.

00:16:00.520 --> 00:16:01.560
So that's great.

00:16:01.560 --> 00:16:04.020
And as I mentioned,
hybrid diesel electric.

00:16:04.020 --> 00:16:04.920
That's very common.

00:16:04.920 --> 00:16:09.030
I think it's being the
preferred bus mode now, so

00:16:09.030 --> 00:16:12.780
preferred energy system or
propulsion system for buses.

00:16:12.780 --> 00:16:15.630
So often how this works is
that you have a diesel--a clean

00:16:15.630 --> 00:16:19.080
diesel engine, that powers
an electric generator,

00:16:19.080 --> 00:16:20.370
which stores electric energy.

00:16:20.370 --> 00:16:23.400
And then on each wheel,
you have electric motors.

00:16:23.400 --> 00:16:26.250
So, in fact, the propulsion
directly is electric.

00:16:26.250 --> 00:16:30.870
And you're only using the
motor to generate electricity.

00:16:30.870 --> 00:16:33.521
So you can get a lot
of fuel efficiency

00:16:33.521 --> 00:16:35.520
from that, especially
because all of these buses

00:16:35.520 --> 00:16:36.260
stops so often.

00:16:36.260 --> 00:16:36.760
Right?

00:16:36.760 --> 00:16:39.000
They have very-- a
lot of stop and go.

00:16:39.000 --> 00:16:42.990
And so sometimes you
can just kill the engine

00:16:42.990 --> 00:16:45.880
when the bus is stopped.

00:16:45.880 --> 00:16:47.980
All right, what about control?

00:16:47.980 --> 00:16:50.470
So we talked about guidance,
which is lateral control.

00:16:50.470 --> 00:16:52.340
What about longitudinal control?

00:16:52.340 --> 00:16:55.450
So how do you control
when you stop?

00:16:55.450 --> 00:16:58.360
How do you accelerate how
quickly you go or brake?

00:16:58.360 --> 00:17:01.180
So we have manual or visual.

00:17:01.180 --> 00:17:04.690
So buses are typically
driven by a person who

00:17:04.690 --> 00:17:06.310
has a brake and a accelerator.

00:17:06.310 --> 00:17:10.920
And they control everything
manually and on site.

00:17:10.920 --> 00:17:13.780
There is also
manual with signals.

00:17:13.780 --> 00:17:15.880
This is more typically for rail.

00:17:15.880 --> 00:17:18.430
You have signals that
might set a limit, a speed

00:17:18.430 --> 00:17:20.560
limit on the vehicle
and protect trains

00:17:20.560 --> 00:17:22.750
from crashing into each other.

00:17:22.750 --> 00:17:24.250
And then there's
fully automatic.

00:17:24.250 --> 00:17:28.780
So you have a robot controlling
the longitudinal movement

00:17:28.780 --> 00:17:29.710
of the vehicle.

00:17:29.710 --> 00:17:32.650
Questions on these technologies?

00:17:32.650 --> 00:17:34.540
We'll see some examples.

