Let's talk about bus.

00:28:24.560 --> 00:28:25.143
What is a bus?

00:28:25.143 --> 00:28:27.595
And [INAUDIBLE] we're talking
about the stereotypical--

00:28:27.595 --> 00:28:29.720
this is the what is a bus,
what is a train lecture.

00:28:29.720 --> 00:28:35.290
So this is the stereotypical
description of what a bus is.

00:28:35.290 --> 00:28:39.630
But of course, the boundaries
between these modes are blurry.

00:28:39.630 --> 00:28:42.230
So stereotypical
definitions are of vehicle

00:28:42.230 --> 00:28:44.690
operating individually
with rubber tires

00:28:44.690 --> 00:28:47.270
with manual lateral and
manual longitudinal control,

00:28:47.270 --> 00:28:49.630
so a driver has full control.

00:28:49.630 --> 00:28:50.330
Sizes.

00:28:50.330 --> 00:28:54.290
They can be small like a minibus
can carry 10 to 20 passengers.

00:28:54.290 --> 00:28:56.900
And you could go up to
bi-articulated carrying

00:28:56.900 --> 00:29:00.920
as much as a light rail system,
a light rail train, so up

00:29:00.920 --> 00:29:02.280
to 250 passengers.

00:29:02.280 --> 00:29:05.990
If you at systems like
Curitiba in Brazil.

00:29:05.990 --> 00:29:08.731
Vehicle design, you can have
high floor design or low floor

00:29:08.731 --> 00:29:09.230
design.

00:29:09.230 --> 00:29:11.880
Can somebody suggest
what the difference is

00:29:11.880 --> 00:29:15.180
and what the benefit
of low floor is?

00:29:15.180 --> 00:29:15.680
Eli?

