00:55:22.243 --> 00:55:23.540
Rail versus bus.

00:55:23.540 --> 00:55:27.610
So rail has higher capacity.

00:55:27.610 --> 00:55:29.470
Bus has a lower capital costs.

00:55:29.470 --> 00:55:34.549
It's cheaper to buy a bus than
to buy a rail or to build rail.

00:55:34.549 --> 00:55:37.090
Buses, you buy the vehicle and
the streets are already there.

00:55:37.090 --> 00:55:40.570
So you're not having
to build stations.

00:55:40.570 --> 00:55:42.670
The unit operating costs
are lower for rail.

00:55:42.670 --> 00:55:45.610
So if you look at the
average, and we'll

00:55:45.610 --> 00:55:49.540
look at some of these costs,
unit cost by say, by trip,

00:55:49.540 --> 00:55:50.950
by passenger trip.

00:55:50.950 --> 00:55:54.970
Because so many people ride
rail, it's cheaper per ride

00:55:54.970 --> 00:55:58.780
to provide rail
than to provide bus.

00:55:58.780 --> 00:56:02.870
Bus, however, can
cover a wider network

00:56:02.870 --> 00:56:05.050
because it's more flexible.

00:56:05.050 --> 00:56:06.940
Rail tends to better
service quality.

00:56:06.940 --> 00:56:08.410
Because it doesn't have traffic.

00:56:08.410 --> 00:56:10.300
And it has a dedicated
right of way.

00:56:13.400 --> 00:56:14.510
So, yeah.

00:56:14.510 --> 00:56:16.790
And it has a stronger
land-use influence.

00:56:16.790 --> 00:56:18.790
Because the stations are in map.

00:56:18.790 --> 00:56:21.620
And you sort of know
the rail map of the city

00:56:21.620 --> 00:56:25.710
much faster than you learn
about its bus network.

00:56:25.710 --> 00:56:29.420
So there's a bias that people
have towards taking rail

00:56:29.420 --> 00:56:32.030
over taking bus, even if
rationally taking a bus

00:56:32.030 --> 00:56:32.960
would be faster.

00:56:32.960 --> 00:56:37.960
You may not even be aware
of all of your bus options.

00:56:37.960 --> 00:56:40.160
And fewer negative
externalities.

00:56:40.160 --> 00:56:43.120
That's because electricity
that powers these is often

00:56:43.120 --> 00:56:45.650
generated outside of
the city and brought in.

00:56:45.650 --> 00:56:50.410
So the air pollution cost by
the consumption of electricity

00:56:50.410 --> 00:56:52.270
for rail is not--

00:56:52.270 --> 00:56:56.930
is not an externality that is
internalized in the city often,

00:56:56.930 --> 00:56:58.780
if that makes sense.

00:56:58.780 --> 00:57:00.160
So, right.

00:57:00.160 --> 00:57:03.170
So bus is much more flexible.

00:57:03.170 --> 00:57:06.680
And you can operate it
on any road [INAUDIBLE]

00:57:06.680 --> 00:57:11.100
or on a guided right-of-way
or a designated right-of-way.

00:57:11.100 --> 00:57:13.570
And it's more
prone to being used

00:57:13.570 --> 00:57:15.830
in [INAUDIBLE]
mode nature, right?

00:57:15.830 --> 00:57:18.540
So just the flexibility.

